## Memory system

This workspace uses a 4-layer memory architecture managed by `save-context-kit`:

| Layer | File | Role | Volatility |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Identity** | `CLAUDE.md` (this file) | Who I am, how I work | Stable, rare edits |
| **Critical context** | `{{CRITICAL_CONTEXT_FILE}}` (per project, in `{{SESSIONS_DIR}}/{project}/`) | Locked decisions, architecture, learnings | Edits per planning session |
| **Working memory** | `{{WORKING_MEMORY_FILE}}` | This week's priorities, hot items | Weekly |
| **Episodic** | `{{SESSIONS_DIR}}/{project}/NN-*.md` | Session changelog (what happened, when) | Append-only |

Use:
- `/save-context` to save the current session. Writes a session log with a Resume highlights block at the top.
- `/resume` to pick up. Reads MASTER.md + Resume highlights, then verifies state against reality before reporting.

See [PHILOSOPHY.md](./PHILOSOPHY.md) (in the save-context-kit repo) for the why behind this architecture.

